#### [Dimensionality reduction](/Dimensionality_reduction)

Simplifying the complex.

*   **[Factor analysis](/Factor_analysis):** Identifying underlying latent variables.
*   **[CCA (Canonical Correlation Analysis)](/Canonical_correlation):** Finding relationships between two sets of variables.
*   **[ICA (Independent Component Analysis)](/Independent_component_analysis):** Separating a multivariate signal into additive subcomponents. Like unscrambling a broadcast.
*   **[LDA (Linear Discriminant Analysis)](/Linear_discriminant_analysis):** Used for classification and dimensionality reduction.
*   **[NMF (Non-negative Matrix Factorization)](/Non-negative_matrix_factorization):** Decomposing a matrix into two non-negative matrices. Useful for feature extraction.
*   **[PCA (Principal Component Analysis)](/Principal_component_analysis):** Finding the directions of maximum variance in data. The most popular way to simplify.
*   **[PGD (Proper Generalized Decomposition)](/Proper_generalized_decomposition):** A method for tensor decomposition.
*   **[t-SNE (t-distributed Stochastic Neighbor Embedding)](/T-distributed_stochastic_neighbor_embedding):** Primarily for visualizing high-dimensional data. Making the abstract visible.
*   **[SDL (Sparse Dictionary Learning)](/Sparse_dictionary_learning):** Learning a dictionary of basis elements for sparse representations.

***

#### [Structured prediction](/Structured_prediction)

Beyond single labels.

*   **[Graphical models](/Graphical_model):** Representing complex relationships between variables using graphs.
*   **[Bayes net (Bayesian network)](/Bayesian_network):** A probabilistic graphical model representing a set of random variables and their conditional dependencies.
*   **[Conditional random field](/Conditional_random_field):** A discriminative undirected graphical model.
*   **[Hidden Markov model](/Hidden_Markov_model):** A statistical model where the system being modeled is assumed to be a Markov process with unobserved (hidden) states.

***

#### [Anomaly detection](/Anomaly_detection)

The art of finding what's *wrong*.

*   **[RANSAC (Random Sample Consensus)](/Random_sample_consensus):** An iterative method to estimate parameters of a mathematical model from an observed set of data that contains outliers.
*   **k -NN:** Can also be used to find outliers based on their distance to neighbors.
*   **[Local outlier factor](/Local_outlier_factor):** Measures the local density deviation of a data point with respect to its neighbors.
*   **[Isolation forest](/Isolation_forest):** An algorithm that isolates anomalies by randomly partitioning the data.

