#### [Reinforcement learning](/Reinforcement_learning)

Learning through consequence.

*   **[Q-learning](/Q-learning):** An algorithm that learns the value of taking an action in a given state.
*   **[Policy gradient](/Policy_gradient_method):** Directly optimizing the policy that the agent uses.
*   **[SARSA (State–action–reward–state–action)](/State%E2%80%93action%E2%80%93reward%E2%80%93state%E2%80%93action):** An on-policy temporal difference learning algorithm.
*   **[Temporal difference (TD)](/Temporal_difference_learning):** Learning from the difference between predictions at different time steps.
*   **[Multi-agent](/Multi-agent_reinforcement_learning):** When multiple agents interact in an environment. A digital ecosystem.
*   **[Self-play](/Self-play_(reinforcement_learning_technique)):** Agents learning by playing against themselves. A recursive path to mastery.

