*   **[Empirical risk minimization](/Empirical_risk_minimization):** A principle for learning models by minimizing the error on the training data.
*   **[Occam learning](/Occam_learning):** The principle that simpler explanations are generally better.
*   **[PAC learning (Probably Approximately Correct learning)](/Probably_approximately_correct_learning):** A theoretical framework for analyzing learning algorithms.
*   **[Statistical learning](/Statistical_learning_theory):** The theory behind learning from data using statistical methods.
*   **[VC theory (Vapnik–Chervonenkis theory)](/Vapnik%E2%80%93Chervonenkis_theory):** A theory for analyzing the capacity of statistical learning algorithms.
*   **[Topological deep learning](/Topological_deep_learning):** Applying concepts from topology to deep learning.

